               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary"> This very rare, complete manuscript of the
                        <title>Rang-i Bahār</title> (Colour of Spring), also known as the
                        <title>Farhang-i Bahār-i Dānish</title> (Dictionary of the <title>Bahār-i
                        Dānish</title>) first composed by a little-known author named ‘Abd al-Bāqī
                     in <date>1160 AH (1747 CE)</date>, contains a glossary of terms found in the
                     romance <title>Bahār-i Dānish</title> (Spring of Wisdom) by <persName
                        key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">‘Inayāt
                        Allāh</persName>. Completed in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1820"
                        to="1821">1236 AH (1820–21 CE)</date>, over 70 years after its completion,
                     it appears to be the earliest-known suriving copy.</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_477-item1">
                     <locus from="1b" to="26a">1b to 26a</locus>
                     <author role="cmm" key="person_f4663"><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Abd
                           al-Bāqī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">عبد الباقي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author role="ant" key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">ʻInāyat Allāh, d. ca.
                           1671</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">‘Ināyat Allāh Kanbū
                           Lāhūrī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Kanbū, ‘Ināyat
                        Allāh</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عنايت الله</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">عنايت الله كنبو لاهوری</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">كنبو، عنايت الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="scr"><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mīrzā Aḥmad Jān</persName>; <lb/>
                     <persName xml:lang="fa">میرزا احمد جان</persName></editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7106">Rang-i Bahār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7106">رنگ بهار</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7106">Farhang-i Bahār-i
                        Dānish</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa" key="work_7106">فرهنگ بهار دانش</title>

                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla">
                        <locus from="1b" to="1b">برگ ۱پ (Folio 1b):</locus>   بعد از تشريح حمد طرازی
                        مصنف مجموعهٔ عالم و توضيح ثناپردازی معلمِ ما لا يعلم نعت ديباچه آرای اول ما
                        خلق و محمدت خاتمه. </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus from="26a" to="26a">برگ ۲۶ر (Folio 26a):</locus> هر جا گه خواهد بود
                        خواهد یافت شما را مرگ اگرچه باشید شما در جبا(؟) محکم پیداشتم مقعول است از
                        شنید نبودن(؟) یفعل تا خور از رشید </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="26a" to="26a">برگ ۲۶ر (Folio 26a):</locus> تمام شد فرهنگ بهار
                        دانش مسمی برنگ بهار بدست عاصی میرزا احمد جان بتاریخ بیست جهارم شهر صفر سنه
                        ۱۲۳۶ هجری اتمام یافت. نوشته بماند سیه بر سفید * نویسنده را نیست فردا امید.
                        تم تم تم تمت تمام شد. </colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName role="scr">Mīrzā Aḥmad Jān</persName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1820-12-20">24 Ṣafar 1236 AH (20 Dec. 1820)</date> </colophon>

                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>The only other documented copy of this work appears in ‘Ārif Nawshāhī's
                        catalogue, held in Karachi, Hamdard University MS D4-11, completed on
                           <date>19 Ramaz̤ān 1253 AH (17 Dec. 1837)</date>. For copies of the
                           <title>Bahār-i Dānish</title> held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7392"><idno>Persian
                              MS 88</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6678">199</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6980"
                           >463</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7430">919</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26591"
                           >991</ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26536"
                        >1017</ref>.</note>

                  </msItem>
